A Hogmanay party attacker was jailed for five years and four months after a woman jumped 15ft from a broken window to escape him. Thug jailed after woman jumps 15ft from a broken window to escape him A Hogmanay party attacker was jailed for five years and four months after a woman jumped 15ft from a broken window to escape him.Michael Newlands had threatened to murder his victim, Selena Jeffrey, the High Court in Edinburgh heard.Newlands, 24, from Lochgilphead, admitted the assault at a flat in Overtown Street, Glasgow. 